			<div class="content" id="post-content-4509004">
									

<p>Copying this from IRC:</p>
<p>Prostitution is illegal in Vegas (and the rest of Clark County). Illegal prostitution is a major issue for the city, they crack down on it super hard—establishments especially cannot survive.</p>
<p>But it's still a 5bn industry, because the in-city prostitutes seek out clients in other casinos. So here's a suggestion: instead of being a brothel, have it be a small mini-casino or other establishment where prostitutes are commonly known to pick up clients. Because that is super, super common in Clark.</p>

