				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/t-rutherford" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4620432); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4620432&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205809" alt="T Rutherford" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4620432)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/t-rutherford" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4620432); return false;" >T Rutherford</a></span> <span class="odate time_1582213133 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Feb 2020 15:38</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4509021">
									

<p>Son of a- I fell asleep after work yesterday. I had my crit all typed up this morning and WHAMMO. ITS ON THE FRONT PAGE!</p>
<p>Oh well, here it is.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">My&nbsp;late,&nbsp;late&nbsp;crit.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">So&nbsp;late.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>&quot;SCP-5690 is a brothel located in the city of Las Vegas. SCP-5690 is staffed almost entirely by Ardor-class demonic entities, characterized by a specialty toward the third Cardinal Vice, lust. SCP-5690 currently employs 16 Ardor-class entities.&quot;</p>
<p>Maybe I'm missing it, but aren't Incubi also classified under Ardor-Class? So, why &quot;almost entirely&quot;? is there a mention of mortal prostitutes also working there? If not, couldn't it be condensed down to &quot;currently staffed by 16 Ador-Class entities, characterized by a specialty&#8230;&quot; ?</p>
<p>The second addendum might have more punch if the line was logged as an after-action report, creating the required unknown gap in time for them to, well, &quot;confirm&quot; it's a brothel.</p>
<p>Besides that, it does lack a certain level of escalation. The dip from the second addendum works fine, but I feel like there should be an incident, or some instigating event that requires the third interview beyond just, well, an excuse for more exposition. There doesn't seem to be a reason for the third addendum at all - the foundation is already aware of the brothel, what it does, etc. Even some minor incident as an excuse to bring the &quot;Matron&quot; in for questioning would provide the right amount of escalation.</p>
<p>Beyond that, the twist ending is super cute, but a bit out of left field. It opens up a lot of possibilities really quickly (i.e. Big J is up and about and getting his freak on) but shuts them just as soon. It's a good twist, just jarring.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>+1, but the narrative pacing is a bit of a drunk walk.</p>
<p>P.S. Per the whole Illegal Prostitution argument - this isn't Vegas, it's Sin City, Undervegas, Hell Vegas, whatever. The establishing universe set out by 4661 means that I can absolutely believe this new Vegas quickly turned around on the brothel argument.</p>

							</div>

								
