			<div class="content" id="post-content-4509065">
									

<p>0 from me.</p>
<p>I really enjoyed myself reading it, and it was undeniably funny. However, the camp factor is keeping me from the upvote. To my mind, the name of the game is verisimilitude when it comes to SCP articles in particular. And what keeps me from getting there isn't the fact that this is a brothel or the fact that a Foundation agent went to one, or even that a demonic madame would charge for her time.</p>
<p>What keeps me from getting there is the consistent use of comedic writing tropes in the transcripts. Funny is one thing, but in this case the piece is too self-aware of its comedy to read as a natural event. That's what I'm looking for when I crack open a skip. So I'm sorry, but I don't feel right upvoting it in its current form.</p>
<p>I reckon you could get it there with a bit of work on those transcripts, though.</p>

